  "text": "The SpiderMonkey JIT compilation pipeline is defined across multiple key C++ files in the mozilla-firefox/firefox repository. The top-level Ion optimizing compiler is orchestrated by the IonCompile() function (mozilla-firefox/firefox:js/src/jit/Ion.cpp, line 1765), which drives the entire compilation process. This function coordinates all phases of Ion optimization and code generation. Off-thread compilation is handled by the IonCompileTask class (mozilla-firefox/firefox:js/src/jit/IonCompileTask.h, line 27), which represents a single asynchronous compilation task that runs on helper threads. The implementation details are in IonCompileTask.cpp. The first-tier JIT compiler is defined by the BaselineScript class (mozilla-firefox/firefox:js/src/jit/BaselineJIT.h, line 189), which stores the baseline JIT-compiled code and metadata for a script. Global JIT runtime state is managed by the JitRuntime class (mozilla-firefox/firefox:js/src/jit/JitRuntime.h, line 121), which maintains per-runtime JIT infrastructure including IC stubs, trampoline code, and compilation task management. JIT configuration options are defined by DefaultJitOptions struct and the global JitOptions variable (mozilla-firefox/firefox:js/src/jit/JitOptions.h, line 182), which control various optimization and compilation thresholds. Together, these components form the complete JIT compilation pipeline from bytecode to optimized native code."
}

